S. Korea’s Kwon Says Banks Capable of Absorbing Short-Term Shock

-- B y   S e o n j i n   C h a
-- 
2011-08-11T06:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/s-korea-s-kwon-says-banks-capable-of-absorbing-short-term-shock.html
South Korea ’s banks are capable of
absorbing short-term shocks because they have sufficient cash
assets and access to enough foreign currency, Financial
Supervisory Service Governor Kwon Hyouk Se told reporters today.
Still, banks need to diversify their funding sources and should
also look to the  Middle East  and emerging markets, Kwon said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
